---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const offer = [
  'Clarity and explanations in plain words, no jargon',
  'Concrete steps for real situations, in the order that matters',
  'Cited sources you can verify yourself',
  'Real numbers and links where you can report a problem in Romania',
  'Free access — no account, no payment, no tracking',
];

const dontOffer = [
  'Diplomas, certificates or attestations',
  'Authority badges or professional status',
  'Career or job promises',
  'Institutional recognition',
  'Compliance theatre',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why we exist"
  description="We are not a certification academy. We are a public tool for understanding and adapting to the digital world. Here is what we offer — and what we do not."
  alternates={{ ro: '/de-ce-existam', en: '/en/why-we-exist', hu: '/hu/miert-letezunk' }}
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why we exist</span>
      <h1>We do not offer diplomas. We offer clarity.</h1>

      <div class="content">
        <p class="lead">
          We build this platform for the person who has to adapt to a digital
          world that changes faster than institutions manage to explain it.
        </p>

        <p>
          There is a lot of talk about digitalisation, cybersecurity, "digital
          skills" and resilience. Public money is spent on speeches and
          strategies. But far too often, when an ordinary person actually has a
          problem — a hacked account, a scam, a fraud call — they do not find a
          clear, public, practical path. They find closed pages, jargon, or
          silence.
        </p>

        <p>
          We are not saying everything should be public. In security, some
          content must stay controlled. But if we talk publicly about a
          "digital skills deficit", then ordinary people deserve at least one
          simple, accessible tool. That is the gap we cover. We do not replace
          institutions — we fill in what is missing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="offer-grid">
        <section class="offer offer-yes" aria-labelledby="oferim">
          <h2 id="oferim">What we offer</h2>
          <ul>
            {offer.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="offer offer-no" aria-labelledby="nu-oferim">
          <h2 id="nu-oferim">What we do NOT offer</h2>
          <ul>
            {dontOffer.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="content closing">
        <p>
          The goal is not to hand you a diploma. The goal is to make you less
          vulnerable, better informed and more capable in the world you live
          in. The value is not at the end, in a certificate — it is in every
          page, every step, in the moment you say:
          <strong>"Now I know what to do."</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    max-width: 18ch;
  }
  .content {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
  .offer-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    margin-block: var(--space-6);
  }
  @media (min-width: 44rem) {
    .offer-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
  .offer {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .offer h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }
  .offer ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .offer li {
    padding-left: 1.8rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .offer-yes {
    background: var(--color-safe-soft);
    border-color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--color-safe) 35%, transparent);
  }
  .offer-yes h2 {
    color: var(--color-safe-text);
  }
  .offer-yes li::before {
    content: '✓';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
    color: var(--color-safe);
  }
  .offer-no {
    background: var(--color-surface-2);
  }
  .offer-no li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
  .closing {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-accent-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }
</style>
